# ~/.localrc — machine-specific configuration, not tracked by git
# Copy this file to ~/.localrc and uncomment the values you want to change.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Language
# Language for dotfiles shell functions (extract/extraer, compress/comprimir).
# Supported: en (default), es
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOTFILES_LANG="en"     # "es" enables: extraer=extract, comprimir=compress

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Login banner
# Show the dotfiles logo on shell login.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOTFILES_SHOW_LOGO=0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Privilege escalation
# Prefix for package manager commands. Leave unset to use sudo by default.
# Set to "" to run without sudo (e.g. if you are root).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IFSUDO="sudo"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default applications
# Used by file extension associations in zsh (alias -s).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BROWSER="firefox"
if command -v emacs >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  EDITOR="emacs"
else
  EDITOR="vim"
fi
# VISOR="feh"
# OFFICESUITE="libreoffice"
# PDFVIEWER="papers"          # GNOME 3+; use "evince" on older systems
# GIMP="gimp"
# SVG_EDITOR="inkscape"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Projects directory
# Base path for your code projects.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PROJECTS="$HOME/Projects"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pager
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PAGER="less"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Display resolution toggle (`res` function)
# `res` detects your backend automatically — you do NOT need to know its flags:
#   macOS         displayplacer   (brew install displayplacer)
#   Linux/X11     xrandr          (covers XFCE, LXQt, GNOME-on-Xorg)
#   Linux/Wayland wlr-randr (wlroots/sway) | gnome-randr (GNOME) | kscreen-doctor (KDE)
# Run `res` with nothing configured to print the current layout and find your
# output name. (Plain xrandr is a no-op under Wayland, so GNOME/Wayland needs
# gnome-randr installed; without it `res` points you to Settings.)
#
# HIGH-LEVEL (recommended) — just give the output and two resolutions as WxH
# (optionally WxH@Hz); res builds the right command for whatever backend it found:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RES_OUTPUT="eDP-1"      # on macOS this is the displayplacer screen id
# RES_A="1440x900"
# RES_B="1920x1080"
#
# RAW (advanced, overrides the high-level vars) — pass native backend arguments
# verbatim, for scaling/rotation/multi-monitor that the high-level form can't express:
# RES_MODE_A="--output eDP-1 --mode 1440x900"                       # xrandr/wlr-randr/gnome-randr
# RES_MODE_B="id:XXXX res:1920x1200 scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0" # displayplacer (one quoted string)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local PATH additions
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
